The paper focuses on visually grounded language learning, which involves both computer vision and natural language processing. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses deep learning models and their training, which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of audio data, which could be categorized under cs.SD (Sound). Finally, the paper discusses evaluation metrics and human ratings, which could be categorized under cs.MM (Multimedia).
